        "title": "Cannot Iterate Through 2D List",
        "body": "<p>Okay, so I have my for loop here ...<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>    System.out.println(positions.get(0)[0]);\n    for (int x = 0; x &lt; positions.size(); x++) {\n        System.out.println(\"Spawning monsters! Current level is \" + level);\n        getMap().spawnMonsterOnGroudBelow(mobs.get(level), positions.get(x)[0], positions.get(x)[1]);\n    }\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>It contains an int list inside, but for some reason it stops iterating on the first go around. The size of positions is <strong>10<\/strong>, so I know for a fact that it should iterate 10 things, but on my console it only prints one time when it should print 10 times.<\/p>\n\n<p>When I printed the 2d list itself, I got this ...<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>[[object array], [object array], [object array] ....]\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>I can't access any of the elements in each of the arrays, but I know the arrays exist. So my question is: how come I can't access the elements in each of those arrays? My code just stops the moment I try to.<\/p>\n",
